{"ID":270274, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"274\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs273.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs275.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 274<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">unloose,&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> and Christ came according to the words of John, and He was greater than John,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> because\n  He held the keys of the Melchizedek Priesthood<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> and kingdom of God,<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> and had before revealed the\n  priesthood of Moses,<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> yet Christ was baptized by John to fulfill all righteousness;<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> and Jesus in His\n  teachings says, &ldquo;Upon this rock I will build my Church, and the gates of hell shall not prevail against\n  it.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> What rock? Revelation.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Again he says, &ldquo;Except a man be born of water and of the Spirit, he cannot enter into the\n  kingdom of God;&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> and, &ldquo;heaven and earth shall pass away, but my words shall not pass away.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> If\n  a man is born of water and of the Spirit, he can get into the kingdom of God. It is evident the\n  kingdom of God was on the earth, and John prepared subjects for the kingdom,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> by preaching the\n  Gospel to them and baptizing them,<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> and he prepared the way before the Savior,<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> or came as a\n  forerunner, and prepared subjects for the preaching of Christ;<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> and Christ preached through\n  Jerusalem<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> on the same ground where John had preached; and when the apostles were raised up,\n  they worked in Jerusalem,<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> and Jesus commanded them to tarry there until they were endowed<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span>\n  with power from on high.<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> Had they not work to do in Jerusalem? They did work, and prepared a\n  people for the Pentecost.<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> The kingdom of God was with them before the day of Pentecost, as well\n  as afterwards; and it was also with John, and he preached the same Gospel and baptism that Jesus\n  and the apostles preached after him.<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> The endowment was to prepare the disciples for their missions\n  unto the world.<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Divine Authority Necessary to Make Ordinances Valid<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Whenever men can find out the will of God and find an administrator legally authorized from\n  God, there is the kingdom of God; but where these are not, the kingdom of God is not. All the\n  ordinances, systems, and administrations on the earth are of no use to the children of men,<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> unless\n  they are ordained and authorized of God;<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> for nothing will save a man but a legal administrator; for\n  none others will be acknowledged either by God or angels.<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">I know what I say; I understand my mission and business.<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> God Almighty is my shield;<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span> and\n  what can man do if God is my friend?<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> I shall not be sacrificed until my time comes;<span class=\"footRef\">27<\/span> then I shall\n  be offered freely.<span class=\"footRef\">28<\/span> All flesh is as grass,<span class=\"footRef\">29<\/span> and a governor<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108628\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108628)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108628)\">John 1:27<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108307\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108307)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108307)\">Mark 1:7<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107939\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107939)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107939)\">Matt. 11:11<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116048\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116048)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116048)\">D&amp;C 124:123<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108072\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108072)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108072)\">Matt. 16:19<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114248\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114248)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114248)\">D&amp;C 65:2<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114611\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114611)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114611)\">D&amp;C 84:6,19-25<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107790\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107790)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107790)\">Matt. 3:15<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108065\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108065)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108065)\">Matt. 16:18<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">8. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108645\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"